VALDEZ:           Oh, you over there in Canada.

everything.

VALDEZ:           The Yankees are playing over there in Toronto.

GREGORIO:         No the Yankees are not playing here, Colorado is the one playing.

VALDEZ:           And you didn't go, with the kids? It doesn't matter.

GREGORIO:         No, and I'm going to waste four hours... I'm not a fan.

VALDEZ:           Why not?

GREGORIO:         It takes an hour to get to Toronto, and then the game takes about three hours.

VALDEZ:           Damn.

GREGORIO:         No, I'm here at the "Catarata" (waterfall).

VALDEZ:           I'm leaving to Las Vegas on the 10th.

GREGORIO:         I'm staying at the Sheraton Hotel in front of the waterfall. You haven't seen the

pictures I have taken of the bathroom [Ph]?

                  [Voices overlap]

VALDEZ:           Take pictures and send them to me.

GREGORIO:         They don't have... in order for me to talk to you I have to cross to the park, because

from the hotel the calls don't go through.

VALDEZ:           When you go out take pictures so I can see them, I might go over there.

GREGORIO:         I'm going to post them online the thing is that in order to post them I have to be in a

place where I can get internet. I have posted

VALDEZ:           Yes.

GREGORIO:         But go figure, we came here to eat and to drink Canadian beers.

Social conversation about Canada continues. GREGORIO tells VALDEZ that they're being treated like
kings.

VALDEZ:           We're going to the girl's party, the sweet fifteen, me and 9-8. When are you coming back?

is it?

GREGORIO:         Six hours and something.

GREGORIO:         She drove a little bit, almost at the end, straight down. But...

was expired. And here you have to show your passport.

VALDEZ:           Where do you have to show the passports?

country.

VALDEZ:           Yes, I know.

pass, that's not a problem is either your passport

GREGORIO:         You can take a plane to Toronto. And from Toronto you come here.

VALDEZ:           I'll rent a car over there. A few days over there with the wife. Is Jose with you?

GREGORIO:         Yes. They're in their rooms. We're going down to have breakfast now.

want someone with money. What          do you think about that? Can one invest with those people or not?

GREGORIO:         I don't know, I haven't seen the video because there's no internet here.

that stuff? With the fifteen's?" "Yes." So I told him;"I got them for eight- fifty." I got too far ahead of myself,
he told me; "All right fine." Had I known, I would have told him nine or nine- fifty.

GREGORIO:         That's how much Tommy was selling them for, nine- fifty. You must be crazy!

Boston. They bring them up to those people for nineteen.

GREGORIO:         The thirty's.
